Title: twenties
Like: Here's a thought-provoking meme about the significance of the decade we're in. The meme juxtaposes the current 'Twenties' with the 'Roaring Twenties' of the 1920s to highlight the similarities and differences between them. Against the backdrop of poverty, hunger, and global conflict, this meme references the challenges and upheavals of the 1920s. The meme also speaks to the significance of our current decade and the opportunities and challenges we have. In the 21st century, we're facing challenges like climate change and COVID-19. The Great Gatsby intrigues me every time I think about the roaring twenties. Movies, books, and other media have taken advantage of the glamour and excess of the prohibition era.

Title: I went to whole foods and...
Like: This meme shows a Whole Foods employee and a customer talking. The woman insists on grass-fed organic chicken despite employee's explanation that chickens don't eat grass. Consumers get a lot of confusing and contradictory messages about what's healthy and ethical. Making informed food decisions also requires education and awareness. This meme is meant to be a lighthearted reminder to approach the food choices we make with skepticism and the willingness to listen to what others have to say. We can make healthier and more ethical food choices if we know the facts about our food. The meme encourages us to think critically about food messages and make informed food choices based on evidence.

Title: I changed my password to incorrect

I like this meme because it subverts our expectations of what clever and intelligent things should look like. Rather than relying on a complex and secure password, the character in the meme has chosen a deceptively simple approach that enables them to outwit both themselves as well as any potential hackers.

Title: my neighbor called the police
Like: I don't know why it's so funny to me but it just is. In Chinese there's a term called "shuai guo", idiom that literally translates to "throwing the wok," and is used to describe the act of blaming someone else for one's own mistake or problem. It is similar to the English expression "passing the buck," which means to shift the responsibility or blame onto someone else.

Title: gemini
Like: I used to be kinda into gemini boys, and this meme is about how geminis are either oversharing or not talking at all. My experience with geminis is that they can be both outgoing and communicative, sharing their thoughts and feelings readily, or quiet and reserved, guarding their inner worlds tightly. There is little in between - either all in or all out. There is no sign that is capable of capturing the complexity of human personality, of course. Although I gave this meme a 5, I gotta say that speculation about traits associated with different zodiac signs can be fun, but we should always avoid stereotypes.

Title: thank you jesus for the food
Like:
This is quite ironic since the food are provided farmers. rom a young age, I was taught to appreciate and honor farmers' hard work. The food on our table is made possible by their sweat and dedication. In spite of being a Christian, I find this lesson to be valuable and meaningful, reminding me of the importance of humility, gratitude, and respect.

The challenges farmers face don't always result from natural forces or market fluctuations. It can be difficult for farmers to make ends meet and support their families due to political and economic factors.
